Q.6) write a code to calculate simple intrest 

ans:-// to calculate simple intrest
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int p,r,n;
    printf("enter p");
    scanf("%d", &p);
    
    printf("enter r");
    scanf("%d", &r);
    
    printf("enter n");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    
    
    printf("simple intrest is : %d", (p*r*n) /100);
    return 0;
}

explaination:-

//               -for a statement
int             -to define a variable 
scanf        -to take input
%d            -defines that side is integer
&               -shows the location of variable 
